  <span id="freeText2783142053549501901" style="display:none">"Helpless infants, abandoned derelicts, lepers and the terminally ill are the raw material for demonstrations of compassion. They are in no position to complain, and their passivity and abjection is considered a sterling trait. It is time to recognize that the world's leading exponent of this false consolation is herself a demagogue, an obscurantist and a servant of earthly powers." ~Christopher Hitchens<br /><br />Where Mother Teresa is concerned, there is a professed philosophy and a corresponding public perception ...and then there is a profoundly abject reality that screams pretense, deceit and hypocrisy.</span>
